        <ul>
            <li>Participants were informed about disaster causes, risk management, and emergency response strategies.</li>
            <li>Detailed insights were provided about the Disaster Management Act, 2005.</li>
            <li>Techniques for community capacity building to reduce disaster risk were shared.</li>
            <li>Practical demonstrations of first aid and casualty carrying methods (e.g., fireman lift, hand seats).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Advanced Training Techniques Section -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2>Practical Training Highlights</h2>
        <p>Experts guided participants on how to create improvised stretchers using locally available materials such as poles, blankets, and jackets. Techniques for performing CPR in emergencies were also demonstrated, emphasizing life-saving actions during critical situations.</p>

